client: costandusagereportserviceclient # now client usage is checked by mypy and ide should provide code completion ``` ### paginators annotations `types_aiobotocore_cur.paginator` module contains type annotations for all paginators. ```python from aiobotocore.session import get_session from types_aiobotocore_cur import costandusagereportserviceclient from types_aiobotocore_cur.paginator import types should be correctly discovered by mypy and ides describe_report_definitions_paginator: describereportdefinitionspaginator = ( client.get_paginator("describe_report_definitions") ) ``` ### deletereportdefinitionrequestrequesttypedef def get_value() -> deletereportdefinitionrequestrequesttypedef: return {...} ``` ## how it works fully automated [mypy-boto3-builder](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder) carefully generates type annotations for each service, patiently waiting for `aiobotocore` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `aiobotocore` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `aiobotocore` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation is provided for every method. - code is processed by [black](https://github.com/psf/black) and [isort](https://github.com/pycqa/isort) for readability. ## what's new ### implemented features - fully type annotated `boto3`, `botocore`, `aiobotocore` and `aioboto3` libraries - `mypy`, `pyright`, discovery of types for `client.get_waiter` and `client.get_paginator` calls - auto discovery of types for `serviceresource` and `resource` collections - auto discovery of types for documentation_summary: The HTML text describes the PyPI (Python Package Index) listing for "types-aiobotocore-cur" version 2.12.1, released on March 5, 2024. This package provides type annotations for the aiobotocore.CostandUsageReportService 2.12.1 service, aiding in compatibility with various IDEs and tools like VSCode, PyCharm, Emacs, Sublime Text, mypy, and pyright. It's generated with mypy-boto3-builder 7.23.2 and requires Python version 3.8 or higher. The package is designed to help find and fix potential bugs by providing explicit type annotations for client and paginator annotations, literals, and type definitions.
